      "side": 1,
      "message": "I see what you mean. The problem is in build as it recognises no JUnit file as a test file. In this case the solution is different and requires the changes in plugins `BUILD` file. Currently it contains:\n\n```\njunit_tests(\n    name \u003d \"git-repo-metrics_tests\",\n    srcs \u003d glob([\"src/test/java/**/*.java\"]),\n    resources \u003d glob([\"src/test/resources/**/*\"]),\n    tags \u003d [\n        \"git-repo-metrics\",\n    ],\n    deps \u003d [\n        \":git-repo-metrics__plugin_test_deps\",\n    ],\n)\n```\n\nand it means that all files under `src/test/java` will be recognised as JUnit tests. One can solve it by changing it into 2 steps:\n1. compile no-test files into test lib\n2. compile and run tests (but depend on test lib)\n\ne.g.:\n\n```\njava_library(\n    name \u003d \"git-repo-metrics_tests_lib\",\n    testonly \u003d True,\n    tags \u003d [\n        \"git-repo-metrics\",\n    ],\n    srcs \u003d glob(\n        [\"src/test/java/**/*.java\"],\n        exclude \u003d [\"src/test/java/**/*Test.java\"],\n    ),\n    deps \u003d [\n        \"git-repo-metrics__plugin_test_deps\",\n    ],\n)\n\njunit_tests(\n    name \u003d \"git-repo-metrics_tests\",\n    srcs \u003d glob([\"src/test/java/**/*Test.java\"]),\n    resources \u003d glob([\"src/test/resources/**/*\"]),\n    tags \u003d [\n        \"git-repo-metrics\",\n    ],\n    deps \u003d [\n        \":git-repo-metrics__plugin_test_deps\",\n        \":git-repo-metrics_tests_lib\",\n    ],\n)\n```\n\nNote that it will have to be extended with `\"src/test/java/**/*IT.java\"` once integration tests are introduced ;)\n\nWhen applied `FakeMetricsCollector` could be turned to package protected class.",
